metadata.name: FAT Christmas #45
metadata.description:
“FAT Christmas” 由三位台灣創作者主導，並且與另外幾位創作者共創部件。包含發行過 Moonlight Impression 的 mido、影像創作者 Graphyni、熱衷 AI 生成的 Fagem。
你可以在這個生成器中獲取 Chang Ming Yao 的 Aka’s Ape 或由 Chi.L 繪製的 AKAZOO Cat，甚至是 roupin_art 的 Dino Ali。
並祝福所有 Tezos 的創作者與藏家，接下來一年能充滿希望。

我們竭盡所能的補充多樣性，確保每次鑄造都是明確且獨特的結果。
在30多種的背景中，包含由創作者提供的特殊款式，如果你足夠幸運，將有機會獲得美麗且獨特的角色 。

角色方面：
Aka’s Ape 包含 8 種 character、8 種 eyes、8 種 mouth、3 種 personality。
Aka Zoo Cat 包含 7 種 character、10 種 eyes、7 種 mouth、5 種  personality。
Dino Ali 包含 26 種 character、5 種 eyes、8 種 mouth、6 種 personality。
所有角色共享超過 20 款頭飾、9 款服裝、10 種服裝印花。
角色前方桌面的三個位置，亦各自包含 10 種以上的配件。

由衷的希望各位都能玩得開心。
祝大家聖誕快樂，新年快樂。

“FAT Christmas” is a collabration of three creators from Taiwan, with parts contributed by creators including mido's “Moonlight Impression”, video creator Graphyni and generative AI enthusiast Fagem.
You can get Aka’s Ape by Chang Ming Yao, AKAZOO  Cat by Chi.L and Dino Ali by roupin_art from the generator.
Blessing to all Tezos creators and collectors, filled with hope in the coming year.

Diversity is replenished in our best effort to ensure apparent and unique results in every mint.
Among over 30 different backgrounds, including special design provided by the creators, you will have a chance to get a gorgeous and unique character if you are lucky enough.

About the characters:
Aka’s Ape includes 8 types of character, 8 types of eyes, 8 types of mouth and 3 types of personality.
Aka Zoo Cat includes 7 types of character, 10 types of eyes, 7 types of mouth and 5 types of personality.
Dino Ali includes 26 types of character, 5 types of eyes, 8 types of mouth and 6 types of personality.
All characters share over 20 headwears, 9 clothes and 10 clothes patterns.
Over 10 decorations will be assigned to 3 positions on the table in front of the character.

Sincerely hope everyone can have fun.
And wishing you all a Merry Christmas and a happy new year.

metadata.name: Terraced #60
metadata.description:
terraced craters
towering mountains
tranquil colors
dimetric

* this is an animated artwork, the animation loops, its duration depends on the piece, it can be paused by pressing 'p'
* this is a somewhat interactive artwork, click and drag to rotate around/above the object, scroll to zoom in/out
* the current view can be downloaded by pressing 'd'

I began exploring terraced reliefs 3 years ago, starting with lines and cellular noise, and eventually flat colors that turned into subtle gradients.
During that time, the visual concept oscillated between minimalism and busy images. I dropped the cellular noise, replacing it with 2D simplex noise modifying points on the dual grid.
The result is finally something that produces the iterations that keep me happy, something soothing and quiet. Spend some time with it, see how the light changes the landscape.

Best viewed in landscape mode, 3/2 or 16/9.

metadata.name: NESTED IDENTITIES #90
metadata.description:
Nested identities redact fingerprints but deeper meaning can still be found.

Nested identifies refers to the idea that a person may have multiple identities that are interconnected and interdependent. These identities may be related to a person's cultural background, ethnicity, nationality, gender, sexual orientation, social class, profession, and other factors. It is possible that a person may want to conceal or redact certain aspects of their identity in order to protect their privacy or to avoid discrimination or persecution. However, even if certain details about a person's identity are hidden or redacted, it may still be possible to infer deeper meaning or understand more about their experiences and perspectives based on the context in which they express themselves and the information that is available.


The concept of nested identities highlights the complexity and multifaceted nature of a person's identity, and how different aspects of identity can intersect and influence each other. It is important to recognize and respect the diversity of identities that people may hold, and to be mindful of the ways in which power dynamics and social context can shape how people present and express their identities. It is also important to recognize that people's identities may evolve and change over time, and that everyone has the right to self-identify and to define their own identity on their own terms.

Press p to download a high quality export.

metadata.description:
###
waves spreading outwards
running from the disturbance
circular fluid
###

Note: this token takes 10-15s to generate.

A study on noise fields. This one invloves layering four rotated copies of itself ontop of each other to get the symmetrical structure you see. The noise is coalesced into bands, which are then filled with a colour based on whether they join the edge, or are isloated in the middle. The pallete is a simple variation of blues. 

The previews of generated images often come out tinted slightly white, due to how fxpreview works. If you open Live and use 's' to save, it will be in its original colors.

metadata.name: Concrete #192
metadata.description:
640 unique sketches of imaginary walls, inspired by the work of Norwegian architect Erling Viksjø (1910–1971) and his artist collaborators. Viksjø designed the Government Quarter in Oslo and invited artists from different disciplines to help design the facades and interiors of the buildings.

Viksjø’s aim was to “soften” modernist architecture. He invented «Natural Concrete», a type of concrete that deliberately exposes the mixed-in stones on its surface to give it warmth and a human touch. In my work, I have similar ambitions—using code instead of concrete.

The different styles of the piece are inspired by, and dedicated to some of the artists who worked together with Viksjø: Jakob Weidemann (~2%), Carl Nesjar (~18%), Odd Tandberg (~30%), and Tore Haaland (~50%).

In live mode, press ‘S’ to save an image at current resolution or ‘P’ to save a high-resolution file at 6000×6000px (this might take a while depending on your hardware).

Original artwork by Andreas Rau · Made with p5.js & glsl · Oslo, 2021

metadata.name: pantonX.3 #137
metadata.description:
pantonX.3
is the third drop of the zukuNFT project, which is dedicated to geometric and minimalist standards of early geometric art.
inspired by the "bauhaus grundkurs" based on the didactic concepts of the bauhaus (1919-1933) and its teachings by johannes itten, paul klee, wassily kandinsky, lászló moholy-nagy and josef albers. the preliminary courses and their basic design tasks dealt syntactically with circle, line and square as well as color, and contrasts.

i am a visual artist and have worked in the field of coding since the early years of processing.
always loved geometric and minimalist art, bauhaus, de stijl, piet mondrian, sol leWitt -- just to name a few -- and last but not least verner panton, have had a influence on my artistic work.

metadata.name: thébaïde #23
metadata.description:
“Thébaïde” is a french word for wild place, remote and peaceful, where to live in a calm retreat. It's also simply a desert and a synonym of solitude. It comes from Thebaid, an arid region of ancient Egypt and Thebes was the capital.

“thébaïde” is my debut on fx(hash), almost one year since my first works minted on Objkt (a series of Indian ink drawings, in January 2022). After learning the basics of creative coding recently, and a few works with this technique, I decided to create a first generative project. With "thébaïde" I chose to express the minimalist and narrative aspects of my artistic approach (though the title and concept emerged at the end). Gradually the work was resonating with philosophical matters I'm obsessed with since years: time, emptiness, human condition, erosion, desire, chance, combining them into a visual metaphor. The view of a vast area, a changing silhouette, an impenetrable monolith or an opening to elsewhere or nothing, day and night and day and night and dawn and dusk — few elements able to compose a meditative and lasting tableau of questions and feelings.

Press “s” in live mode to save the work.
Made with p5js | 2023
Png | 2000 px x 2000 px | 72 ppi

www.antoniowerli.com

metadata.name: Tomorrow #6
metadata.description:
Tomorrow is probably the biggest uncertainty of our lives.

We hang absolutely everything on tomorrow, the beginning of a new life, training, studies, hopes, expectations, dreams, and many other things, the list can be very long.

But how often do our expectations come true?

This year I hope everyone understood that you cannot hope and count on tomorrow, there is no tomorrow, there is only today.
Stop putting everything off until tomorrow, you may just not notice how your life flew by and you ended up not doing so much.

The shape of the circle was not chosen by chance, it represents the cyclical nature of our lives and everything we do.
But even in this there are exceptions, expecting that tomorrow everything will go on the same scenario, everything goes exactly the opposite.

15 palettes.
5 formats.
2 different drawing modes.

Press S for Save Canvas as PNG.

By aleks.ustya, @ALEKUSTN. Made with p5js.
